[B] South Korea: 15 318 confirmed cases, 305 deaths (279 new cases -- 12 imported, 267 locally transmitted)
http://ncov.mohw.go.kr/en/bdBoardList.do?brdId=16&brdGubun=162&dataGubun=&ncvContSeq=&contSeq=&board_i= and http://ncov.mohw.go.kr/

[The 3rd consecutive day with greater than 100 newly confirmed cases. Notices 499 and 500 at https://www.cdc.go.kr/board.es?mid=a30402000000&bid=0030 provide details on clusters as of 15 Aug 2020. These involve multiple clusters, some faith-based, some school-based, and other areas of work or communal gatherings. Of the local transmitted cases, 146 are in Seoul, and 98 are in neighboring Gyeonggi province. - Mod.UBA]

[C] Italy: 253 438 total cases, 35 392 deaths [comparative 7-day averages have gone up by 46.9% from the preceding 7 days]
https://www.albengacorsara.it/doc/dpc-covid19-ita-scheda-regioni-2020-08-15.pdf

[The 7-day average comparison continues to show an increase in confirmed cases consistent with increasing transmission of the virus. - Mods.UBA/MPP]

